# Git Commits

When creating git commits in this project:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` (or any Cursor co-author trailer) to commit messages.
- Use only the commit subject/body the user expects — no extra trailers, footers, or attribution lines.
- If a commit message template or tool suggests adding Cursor as co-author, ignore it.

Example of what **not** to do:

```
Fix store audit score sync.

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
```

Example of what to do:

```
Fix store audit score sync.
```
